<subSubSection box="[136,1096,1784,1811]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1096,1784,1811]" box="[136,1096,1784,1811]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
<heading bold="true" box="[136,1096,1784,1811]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="163" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,1096,1784,1811]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
Key to 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus (1753: 955)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="955" authorityYear="1753" box="[222,715,1784,1811]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[222,483,1784,1811]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">Passiflora mistratensis</emphasis>
and related species
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[753,870,1784,1810]" name="Colombia" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and Mesoamerica.
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="164" pageId="4" pageNumber="163" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,1852,2076]" box="[136,1451,1852,1874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1852,1874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">1. Leaves unlobed, coriaceous to sub-coriaceous in texture ..................................................................................................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,1852,2076]" box="[136,1451,1881,1903]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1881,1903]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">- Leaves three-to-five lobed or lobulate, sub-coriaceous in texture .....................................................................................................6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,1852,2076]" box="[136,1451,1910,1932]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1910,1932]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">2. Leaves and stems hirsute to tomentose, mostly pronounced along the veins and foliar margins ......................................................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,1852,2076]" box="[136,1451,1939,1961]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1939,1961]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">- Leaves and stems glabrous throughout, stems occasionally glaucous ...............................................................................................4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,1852,2076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
3. Leaves and stems densely hirsute. Foliar margins glandular. Sepals densely hirsute abaxially. 
<collectingCountry box="[1108,1203,1968,1990]" name="Colombia" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">Colombia</collectingCountry>
......................................... ........................................................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Masters (1887: 220)" authorityName="Masters" authorityPageNumber="220" authorityYear="1887" box="[1129,1451,1997,2019]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="praeacuta">
<emphasis box="[1129,1250,1997,2018]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">P. praeacuta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Masters, M. T." box="[1256,1451,1997,2019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163" pagination="218" refId="ref4248" refString="Masters, M. T. (1887) Plantae Lehmannianae in Guatemala, Costarica et Columbia collectae. Passifloraceae et Aristolochiaceae. Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 8 (3): 218." type="journal article" year="1887">Masters (1887: 220)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1451,1852,2076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="163">
- Leaves and stems finely tomentose. Foliar margins smooth. Sepals glabrous on both surfaces. 
<collectingCountry box="[1114,1187,2025,2047]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">Mexico</collectingCountry>
........................................... .............................................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Killip (1922: 261)" authorityName="Killip" authorityPageNumber="261" authorityYear="1922" box="[1166,1451,2054,2076]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpusii">
<emphasis box="[1166,1270,2055,2076]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="163">P. purpusii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Killip, E. P." box="[1276,1451,2054,2076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="163" pagination="261" refId="ref4002" refString="Killip, E. P. (1922) New Passifloras from Mexico and Central America. Journal of the Washington Academy of Sciences 12: 261." type="journal article" year="1922">Killip (1922: 261)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,159,411]" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
4. Petioles with two pairs of petiolar nectaries present. Stipules featuring a distinct yellow mucro at the tip. Awns longer than 
<quantity box="[1379,1448,159,181]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="164" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[211,306,188,210]" name="Colombia" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">Colombia</collectingCountry>
.............................................................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Killip" authorityYear="1960" box="[1354,1450,188,210]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="danielii">
<emphasis box="[1354,1450,188,210]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">P. danielii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,159,411]" box="[136,1451,216,239]" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,216,239]" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
- Petioles with 4–6 scattered glands, sometimes 2–3 paired. Awns shorter than 
<quantity box="[950,1017,217,238]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="164" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
......................................................................5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,159,411]" box="[136,1451,245,267]" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,245,267]" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
5. Stipules without mimicry. Awns 
<quantity box="[524,603,246,267]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="164" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7 mm</quantity>
long. Mesoamerica and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[927,1022,245,267]" name="Colombia" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1034,1099,245,267]" country="Colombia" name="Choco" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">Choco</collectingRegion>
)....................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masters" authorityYear="1872" box="[1343,1451,245,267]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oerstedii">
<emphasis box="[1343,1451,245,267]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">P. oerstedii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,159,411]" box="[136,1452,274,296]" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
<keyLead box="[136,1452,274,296]" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
- Stipules mostly without mimicry. Awns a mere 
<quantity box="[666,745,274,296]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="164" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
long. 
<collectingCountry box="[806,901,274,296]" name="Colombia" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">Colombia</collectingCountry>
...................................................... 
<emphasis box="[1233,1452,275,296]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
<taxonomicName authority="Kuethe &amp; Vanderplank, 2022" authorityName="Kuethe &amp; Vanderplank" authorityYear="2022" box="[1233,1373,275,296]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mistratensis" status="sp. nov.">P. mistratensis</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1379,1452,275,296]" pageId="5" pageNumber="164" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,159,411]" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
6. Petioles with two pairs of petiolar nectaries present. Stipules featuring a distinct yellow mucro at the tip. 
<collectingRegion box="[1216,1312,303,325]" country="Colombia" name="Antioquia" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">Antioquia</collectingRegion>
...................... .............................................................................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masters" authorityYear="1887" box="[1354,1450,332,354]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trisulca">
<emphasis box="[1354,1450,332,354]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">P. trisulca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,159,411]" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="164">
- Only a single pair of petiolar nectaries present. Stipules showing no form of egg mimicry (no mucro at tip). 
<collectingRegion box="[1247,1387,361,383]" country="Colombia" name="Cundinamarca" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">Cundinamarca</collectingRegion>
.......... ............................................................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Killip" authorityYear="1930" box="[1362,1450,389,411]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="164" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="smithii">
<emphasis box="[1362,1450,389,411]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="164">P. smithii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
